# üêû bug report

### Description
I am working on one of the application on Angular 9 and implemented the lazy loading for some module.
when i am running this app in local environment. its working fine but when i am creating the new build using **ng build --prod** and publish build on production environment then **routing is not working for lazy loaded modules.**
for local: http://localhost:4200/resident (working) 
production: http://abxxxx.com/resident (not wokring)
- Here resident is default path to render child component.

## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
1. Create a new project using angular cli command
2. added some module and configure the lazy loading in app.routing as below:
- app.rotuing.module.ts
const routes: Routes = [
  {
    path: '',
    component: LoginComponent
  },
  {
    path: 'dashboard',
    component: DashboardComponent
  },
  {
    path: 'resident',
    loadChildren: () => import('./modules/resident/resident.module').then(rm => rm.ResidentModule)
  },
  {
    path: 'supervisor',
    loadChildren: () => import('./modules/oclm-supervisor/oclm-supervisor.module').then(sup => sup.OclmSupervisorModule)
  },
  // otherwise redirect to login page
  { path: '**', redirectTo: '' }
];
3. child routing for resident .
const routes: Routes = [
  {
    path: '',
    children: [
      {
        path: '',
        pathMatch: 'full',
        redirectTo: 'bashboard'
      },
      {
        path: 'bashboard',
        component: DashboardComponent
      }]
}]



